This is how to sorted_list_sum of lst:
   Remember that filtered is []
   Remember that n is lst's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that x is item i in lst
      When x's length is at least 2, then:
         Add filtered to x
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that m is filtered's length
   Do this m times:
      Remember that j is 0
      Do this diff of m and 1 times:
         Remember that k is sum of j and 1
         Remember that a is item j in filtered
         Remember that b is item k in filtered
         Remember that la is a's length
         Remember that lb is b's length
         Remember that swap is 0
         When la is more than lb, then:
            Remember that swap is 1
         End when
         When la is lb, then:
            When tostring of a is more than tostring of b, then:
               Remember that swap is 1
            End when
         End when
         When swap is 1, then:
            Remember that tmp is item j in filtered
            Remember that item j in filtered is item k in filtered
            Remember that item k in filtered is tmp
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
   End do
   The answer is filtered
